The Senator representing Kaduna South Senatorial District, Sen Danjuma La’ah, has won the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) ticket in the just concluded primaries. On May 10, 2022, the PDP nominated La’ah as the new Senate Deputy Minority Whip. Senator La’ah was born on February 16, 1960. He had been the senator representing Kaduna South since 2015. On February 23, 2019, he was again re-elected into office having garnered 268,287 after he defeated the late Yusuf Barnabas Bala of the All Progressives Congress (APC) who had 133,923 votes.